# GQL Complex Problems and Guardrails

- Enforce playbooks from `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/gql-complex-problems-cookbook.md`.
- Enforce anti-pattern blocklist from `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/gql-anti-patterns-blacklist.md`.
- Enforce refusal behavior from `docs/platforms/backend/patterns/gql-refusal-matrix.md`.

## Hard Gates

- No unbounded root-many query.
- No missing principal guard in scoped root parent resolution.
- No bridge logic depending on non-loaded ORM attrs.
- No relaxed depth/include protection without replacement.
- No polymorphic union logic without discriminator mapping.
- No user-input interpolation inside `sequelize.literal(...)`.
- No actor-bound root-one query without ownership scope when using `STATIC`.
- No enum output contract drift (`_X` wrapper output vs `_XValue` filter input).
- No role bridge base without `loadAttr` override (MultiLang/enum resolution is mandatory).

## Checklist Before Final Output

- [ ] security gate passed
- [ ] mapping gate passed
- [ ] pagination gate passed
- [ ] depth/perf gate passed
- [ ] compatibility gate passed
- [ ] enum-wrapper gate passed
- [ ] backend->frontend mirror sync passed (website for customer; cpanel for supervisor)
- [ ] role bridge base contract passed (loadAttr + trans + toEnum + willPrepare)

## Ejtmaa Supervisor/Customer Guardrails

- Supervisor customer list/detail reads stay in `CustomerBridge` with deterministic sort and filter mapping.
- `customerStats.total_count` stays in `CustomerStatsBridge.loadExtra`.
- Customer and supervisor `MeBridge` enforce actor presence in `willPrepare`.
- Enum output uses `_X` wrappers; filter inputs use `_XValue`.
- Reference: `backend/src/app/gql/bridges/supervisor/CustomerBridge.ts`, `CustomerStatsBridge.ts`.
